Key Match Events: Patson Daka scored a late equaliser to salvage a 1-1 draw for 10-man Zambia and deny opponents Tanzania a first Group F win on Sunday.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Late Zambia goal sees Tanzania denied rare win
The match was played at Stade Laurent Pokou in San-Pedro, Ivory Coast, with an attendance of 13,342.
Others: The match ended in a 1-1 draw between Zambia and Tanzania, with Zambia scoring a late equaliser to deny Tanzania a first Group F win.
